      "Great coffee is not about maximising everything. It is about stopping at the right moment. Enough sweetness. Enough body. Enough clarity. Enough complexity. Coffee brewing resembles cooking more than manufacturing. Precision matters. But intuition matters too. And somewhere between sour failure and bitter excess lies the quiet, difficult thing every good café keeps chasing: balance.",
