      "Perhaps the most exciting thing about modern coffee is realising it does not have to taste only one way. Coffee can be comforting, bright, heavy, tea-like, chocolatey, wild, clean, earthy, floral or smoky. No single flavour profile owns legitimacy. And maybe that is why coffee remains endlessly fascinating — because somewhere between a traditional steel tumbler of filter coffee and an anaerobic Ethiopian pour-over exists an enormous flavour universe humans are still learning how to describe properly.",
